# UI Component Usage

Always reach for an existing component from `~/shared/ui/` before writing custom markup. Add only the minimum Tailwind classes needed on top — never re-implement what the component already provides.

## Available components

`Button`, `Badge`, `Card`, `Tabs`, `Tooltip`, `Popover`, `Switch`, `Avatar`, `TextField`, `AlertDialog`

## Rules

- **Use first, style second**: import from `~/shared/ui/`, then layer extra classes via `cn()` only when truly needed.
- **No parallel implementations**: don't recreate a button, badge, card, etc. with plain `<div>`/`<span>` when a shared component exists.
- **Extend via props**: prefer the component's own props (variant, size, …) over overriding with Tailwind.
- **`cn()` for overrides**: when you must add classes, always merge them with `cn()`.

```tsx
// ❌ BAD — reimplements an existing component
<div class="rounded-full bg-primary px-2 py-0.5 text-xs font-semibold text-primary-foreground">
  New
</div>

// ✅ GOOD — uses the shared Badge, one extra class only
import { Badge } from '~/shared/ui/badge'

<Badge variant="default" class={cn('mt-1')}>New</Badge>
```
